 A youth brigade in Johannesburg has one goal in mind - to ensure that eligible people get vaccinated against COVID-19. eNCA's Khayelihle Khumalo reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - As South Africa ramps up its vaccination campaign and targets vulnerable groups, some young people are at the forefront of ensuring people get the jab. The Ahmed Kathrada Foundation’s youth wing has ventured out in Johannesburg to make certain that eligible people register. This forms part of the foundation’s outreach programme. READ: Vaccine refusal concerns Gauteng Education Department While some people are receptive to having their details taken down for vaccinations, others are still hesitant. But activists say they won’t be deterred. * eNCA's Khayelihle Khumalo reports. 